article.description: — Raheem Anthony scored 15 points as St. Thomas beat Omaha 88-61 on Thursday night.
article.headline: St. Thomas secures 88-61 victory against Omaha
article.linkText: St. Thomas secures 88-61 victory against Omaha
article.story: SAINT PAUL, Minn. -- — Raheem Anthony scored 15 points as St. Thomas beat Omaha 88-61 on Thursday night. Anthony added five rebounds, six assists, and three steals for the Tommies (18-12, 8-7 Summit League). Parker Bjorklund scored 14 points and added eight rebounds. Kendall Blue went 5 of 8 from the field to finish with 13 points. The Mavericks (14-17, 7-9) were led by Jaeden Marshall, who posted 13 points and six rebounds. JJ White added 13 points and seven assists for Omaha. Marquel Sutton also had 12 points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
